Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic{3%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #large bowl{}, combine half the garlic, @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Panko Breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{pinch} and @Water{1%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British Beef Mince{240%g}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the meatballs and fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the remaining garlic and @Rogan Josh Curry Paste{50%g}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{100%ml} for the sauce and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}.

Season with salt and pepper, then cover with a #lid{} or #foil{} and simmer until the meatballs are cooked, ~{6-7%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, stir in the @Baby Spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your plates.

Top the rice with the Rogan Josh style curry and meatballs.

Drizzle with @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%g} to finish.

Enjoy!